Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1%unit}. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @yellow onion{1%unit}. Very thinly slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce}.

Toss bell pepper on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast until softened and lightly charred, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably
#nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and
@sugar{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a small
#bowl{}. Wash out pan.

While veggies cook, in a small #pot{}, combine @marinara cup{14%oz},
@veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, 3/4 cup water, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Once boiling, reduce
heat to medium low and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp}
until melted. Cover and continue to simmer until ready to serve.

Heat pan used for onion over medium heat. While pan heats, place
@butter{3%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just
softened, ~{10-20%seconds}. Spread one side of each slice of
@sourdough bread{4%slices} with softened butter. Place buttered sides down on
a work surface. Top half the slices with half the mozzarella, all the veggies,
and remaining mozzarella. Complete sandwiches with remaining slices of bread,
buttered sides up; press firmly.

Place sandwiches in preheated pan; use a #spatula{} to press down. Cook until
bread is golden brown and cheese is melted, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer
to a #cutting board{} and slice in half on a diagonal; divide between plates.
Season soup generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}; divide between #bowls{} and
serve on the side.

> TIP: Dip panini into soup, if you like!